body:
## Steps to reproduce the issue

Consider the following code:
```
module inivalue(i_clk, i_val, o_val);
	input	wire	i_clk;
	input	wire	[2:0]	i_val;
	output	reg	[1:0]	o_val;

	reg	[2:0]	r_val;

	initial	r_val = 0;
	always @(posedge i_clk)
		r_val <= r_val + i_val;

	always @(*)
		o_val = r_val[1:0];

endmodule
```

Notice the unused bits of r_val.

If you process this code with either `yosys -p 'synth_ice40 -top inivalue' inivalue.v` or `yosys -p 'synth_ecp5 -top inivalue' inivalue.v`, yosys will return the warning:

```
Warning: Wire inivalue.r_val has an unprocessed 'init' attribute.
```

This warning suggests that an `initial` attribute has not been applied, when in reality what's taking place appears to be an appropriate optimization.

## Expected behavior

I expect either 1) no warnings if the synthesized design matches the incoming warning, or 2) a more specific warning indicating that the unprocessed init attribute is associated with an unused bit.

## Actual behavior

See the warning above.

